Ogun State Police Command, yesterday, recovered the remains of Oreoluwa Fatinoye, the son of the couple who were killed by yet-to-be-identified assassins in Abeokuta, on New Year day.
   
The deceased was reportedly thrown into a river along the Adigbe – Obada road in Abeokuta, the state capital, after he was kidnapped by the assailants who murdered his parents.
 
The decomposing body of Oreoluwa was discovered floating on the river by fishermen on Tuesday morning, barely 24 hours after his parents were buried 
 
The parents, Kehinde and Bukola Fatinoye were gruesomely murdered in the early hours of Sunday, January 1.  MEANWHILE, the Command’s spokesperson, Abimbola Oyeyemi,  who confirmed the development, said the police had commenced investigation to unravel the mystery behind the death of the Fatinoyes. 